com.analog.lyric.options

Class OptionKey<T extends java.io.Serializable>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.analog.lyric.options.OptionKey<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - is the type of the values of the option indexed by this key.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    IOptionKey<T>, java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BooleanOptionKey, ClassOptionKey, DoubleListOptionKey, DoubleOptionKey, EnumOptionKey, GenericOptionKey, IntegerListOptionKey, IntegerOptionKey, LongOptionKey, StringListOptionKey, StringOptionKey, VariableEliminatorCostListOptionKey

    @Immutable
public abstract class OptionKey<T extends java.io.Serializable>
extends java.lang.Object
implements IOptionKey<T>
    Base implementation of IOptionKey interface.

    This is the preferred base class for implementing option key classes and also provides useful static methods for naming and construction.

    Since:
    0.07

      • forCanonicalName

        public static <T extends java.io.Serializable> IOptionKey<T> forCanonicalName(java.lang.String canonicalName)
        Returns key with specified canonicalName using Java reflection to load the declaring class.

        Because this uses reflection it is not expected to be very fast so it is better to put keys in a OptionRegistry if you need frequent lookup by name.

        Since:
        0.07

      • convertToExternal

        public java.lang.Object convertToExternal(T value)
        Description copied from interface: IOptionKey
        Converts value to an external representation

        Converts value to representation suitable for use in external environments such as MATLAB or Python. Acceptable output types include boxed primitive types, Strings, and arrays of the those.

        It is expected that the returned value can be converted back to the original typed value using IOptionKey.convertToValue(java.lang.Object).

        Specified by:

      • getCanonicalInstance

        @Nullable
public static <T extends java.io.Serializable> IOptionKey<T> getCanonicalInstance(IOptionKey<T> key)
        Returns the canonical instance of key.

        Returns the instance of the key that is publicly declared as a static field of getDeclaringClass() with given name() or returns null if there isn't one.

        This method is implemented using reflection and is not expected to be very fast.

        Since:
        0.07

      • canonicalName

        public static java.lang.String canonicalName(IOptionKey<?> option)
        Computes the fully qualified canonical name of the option.

        This name uniquely identifies the option key. It consists of the fully qualified name of getDeclaringClass() and name() separated by '.'. For instance:

        "com.analog.lyric.dimple.options.SolverOptions.iterations"
        Parameters:
        option - is a non-null option key.
        Since:
        0.07

      • qualifiedName

        public static java.lang.String qualifiedName(IOptionKey<?> option)
        Computes the option name qualified by its simple declaring class name.

        This may be used to disambiguate option keys that may have the same simple name. The name consits of the simple name of the option's declaring class and the name() separated by '.'. For instance:

        "SolverOptions.iterations"

        Parameters:
        option - is a non-null option key.
        Since:
        0.07
